This paper describes the optimization of mechanical and electrical components of a robot team for the Small Size League of RoboCup, as well as software contributions such as vision lost compensation and interception prediction algorithms. These topics are all related to robotics and artificial intelligence, which are covered by the cs.RO and cs.AI sub-categories. Additionally, the paper mentions the use of computer vision techniques such as kalman filtering, which falls under the cs.CV sub-category. The mention of radio communication protocols and the need for secure communication suggests the involvement of systems and control, which are covered by the cs.SY sub-category. Finally, the paper mentions the use of machine learning techniques such as kalman filtering and interception prediction, which are also covered by the cs.LG sub-category.
